Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng briefs the media on allegations of corruptions levelled against the judiciary. JOHANNESBURG - Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng briefs the media on allegations of corruptions levelled against the judiciary. The judiciary has been under attack recently, the latest being allegations on social media about NPA head Shamila Batohi. READ: Mogoeng maintains judiciary is independent Speculations were circulated on social media claiming Batohi received over R1.7-million from the CR17 campaign. The Law Society's labelled such claims as malicious and dangerous, saying it undermines the judiciary.